censorship	英[ˈsensəʃɪp]
美[ˈsensərʃɪp]
n.	审查制度; 审查; 检查;
[例句]The banning of his play decided him to write about censorship
他的戏剧被禁演，这促使他下定决心就审查制度的问题下笔。

cen·sorship
/ˈsensərSHip/
Learn to pronounce
noun
1.
the suppression or prohibition of any parts of books, films, news, etc. that are considered obscene, politically unacceptable, or a threat to security.
"the regulation imposes censorship on all media"
2.
(in ancient Rome) the office or position of censor.
"he celebrated a triumph together with his father and they held the censorship jointly"
